üîê Credential Requirements & Setup Guide
To run FlowGenie ‚Äî No-Code Automation Workflow Builder with real third-party integrations, you need the following credentials stored in environment variables:

| Service              | Credential Required        | Env Variable Name           | Notes                                                             |
|----------------------|----------------------------|-----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Google Sheets API    | Service Account JSON       | GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON | Must share spreadsheet with service account (Editor access).      |
| Google Sheets API    | Spreadsheet ID             | SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID       | Extract from sheet URL (`/d/<THIS>/edit`).                        |
| Google Sheets API    | Sheet Tab Name             | SHEETS_TAB_NAME             | Default is "Sheet1".                                               |
| Gmail API            | Sender (delegated) email   | GMAIL_SENDER_EMAIL          | The Gmail/Workspace account that sends the email.                 |
| Google Calendar API  | Calendar ID (optional)     | CALENDAR_ID                 | Only required if workflow creates calendar events.                |
| Slack                | Incoming Webhook URL       | SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL           | Webhook must belong to a channel where the bot has permission.    |
| Project Settings     | Toggle real API mode       | USE_REAL_APIS               | `true` ‚Üí real integrations, `false` ‚Üí safe simulation & no-ops.   |


Example .env file (complete)
# Turn real APIs ON/OFF
USE_REAL_APIS=true

# Google Sheets
GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type": "service_account", ... full JSON here ...}
SHEETS_SPREADSHEET_ID=1W-QRuaUO78l8WltIZE8B73KetrilHw4hGXKnrshl9Ko
SHEETS_TAB_NAME=Sheet1

# Gmail
GMAIL_SENDER_EMAIL=myemail@gmail.com

# Google Calendar (optional)
CALENDAR_ID=my_calendar_id@group.calendar.google.com

# Slack
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/XXXX/YYYY/ZZZZ


1. Required Google Cloud Configuration (for Sheets / Gmail / Calendar)

~ Create a Google Cloud Project
~Go to APIs & Services ‚Üí Library
~Enable these APIs:
Google Sheets API
Gmail API

2. Google Calendar API

~Google Drive API (helps Sheets access)
~Go to APIs & Services ‚Üí Credentials ‚Üí Create Credentials ‚Üí Service Account
~Once created ‚Üí Keys ‚Üí Add Key ‚Üí JSON
~Copy the entire JSON to environment variable:

  GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON = <full JSON here>

3. Grant Permissions for Sheets & Drive

~Google Sheets WILL NOT work until you do this manually:
Open your target spreadsheet
Click Share
~Add the Service Account email as Editor

<service-account>@<project>.iam.gserviceaccount.com

~This is required ‚Äî otherwise Sheets will respond with:

403 ‚Äî The caller does not have permission

4. Gmail API Delegated Access

Put the email you want to send emails from (usually your Gmail address):

GMAIL_SENDER_EMAIL = yourname@gmail.com


The system sends emails on behalf of this account via the Service Account.
If using personal Gmail: sending works as long as the Gmail API is enabled and the service account has delegated access.

5. Slack Webhook Setup

Go to Slack ‚Üí Apps ‚Üí Incoming Webhooks
Create a webhook URL
Paste it in your .env:

SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL = https://hooks.slack.com/services/...


When FlowGenie triggers Slack actions, messages will post directly in that channel.

üü° Optional: Calendar API

If you want to test Calendar events:
Go to Google Calendar ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Select a calendar ‚Üí Integrate Calendar
Copy Calendar ID

CALENDAR_ID = xxxxxx@group.calendar.google.com

If omitted, the project runs Calendar actions in safe no-op mode instead of failing.

